**Privacy Policy**

**Effective Date:** 29/03/2025

This Privacy Policy describes how your personal information is collected, used, and protected when you use our mobile application ("App"). By using the App, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.

---

**1. Information We Collect**

We may collect the following types of personal information from users:

- **Account login information** (e.g., email address, phone number)
- **Health data** (e.g., uploaded medical records, prescriptions, reports)
- **Precise geolocation data** (used for session security)
- **Device information** (model, OS version, device ID)
- **Language and theme preferences**
- **Session and access logs**

---

**2. How We Use Your Information**

We use personal information to:

- Deliver and facilitate the services offered through the App
- Securely authenticate and manage user accounts
- Store and associate health records with the correct user profile
- Personalize user experience (e.g., theme and language preferences)
- Send important administrative updates or alerts
- Respond to support requests and inquiries
- Maintain the security and integrity of user sessions

---

**3. Legal Basis for Processing**

We process your information under the following legal grounds:

- With your consent
- To fulfill contractual obligations
- To comply with legal obligations
- For legitimate interests, such as security and service improvement

---

**4. Sharing of Personal Information**

We do not sell or rent your personal data. We may share information only under the following conditions:

- With service providers assisting in app functionality (e.g., cloud storage, OTP services)
- To comply with legal or regulatory obligations
- To protect user safety, rights, or our terms of service

---

**5. Data Security**

We implement technical and organizational measures to protect your information, including:

- Encrypted local storage of sensitive data
- Secure login with OTP and session management
- HTTPS and secure APIs for data transmission

---

**6. Data Retention**

Your data will be retained as long as necessary to provide you with our services and as required by applicable laws. You may request deletion of your account and associated data at any time.

---

**7. Your Rights**

Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:

- Access the personal data we hold about you
- Correct or update inaccurate information
- Request deletion of your personal data
- Withdraw consent for processing (where applicable)

To exercise these rights, contact us at: healthvault.co@gmail.com

---

**8. Children's Privacy**

Our App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect data from minors. If we discover that we have unintentionally collected personal information from a child, we will delete it promptly.

---

**9. International Data Transfers**

Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries outside your country of residence. We ensure that appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your data.

---

**10. EEA and UK Users**

We do not currently have a representative in the EEA or UK. If you are located in these regions and have questions about your rights under GDPR, please contact us directly.

---

**11. Changes to This Privacy Policy**

We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "Effective Date" at the top. Continued use of the app after such changes constitutes acceptance.

---

**12. Contact Us**

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: healthvault.co@gmail.com  
Website: https://www.axionhealth.info/

